      "message": "Consider introducing a dedicated POJO for the Gemini input request payload. That would make the contents/parts/text structure more explicit and simplify JSON serialization compared to the current manual JsonObject construction?\n\nSo may be something like this:\n\n```java\npublic class GenerateContentRequest {\n  @SerializedName(\"contents\")\n  private final List\u003cContent\u003e contents;\n\n  public GenerateContentRequest(List\u003cContent\u003e contents) {\n    this.contents \u003d contents;\n  }\n\n  public static GenerateContentRequest fromPrompt(String prompt) {\n    return new GenerateContentRequest(\n        List.of(new Content(List.of(new Part(prompt)))));\n  }\n\n  public List\u003cContent\u003e getContents() {\n    return contents;\n  }\n\n  public static class Content {\n    @SerializedName(\"parts\")\n    private final List\u003cPart\u003e parts;\n\n    public Content(List\u003cPart\u003e parts) {\n      this.parts \u003d parts;\n    }\n\n    public List\u003cPart\u003e getParts() {\n      return parts;\n    }\n  }\n\n  public static class Part {\n    @SerializedName(\"text\")\n    private final String text;\n\n    public Part(String text) {\n      this.text \u003d text;\n    }\n\n    public String getText() {\n      return text;\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThen: this method can be replaced with one liner:\n\n\n```java\nGenerateContentRequest requestBody \u003d GenerateContentRequest.fromPrompt(prompt);\n```",
